.TH DHWEB 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
dhweb \- DigiHub web configuration interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dhweb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dhweb
serves a phone/tablet\-friendly web page for reviewing and editing the
DigiHub configuration stored in
.IR $HOME/.dhinfo ,
as an alternative to the interactive
.BR dhedit (1)
terminal editor. It is a Flask application served by
.B waitress
(a pure\-Python WSGI server), started by the
.B scripts/dhweb
wrapper.
.PP
.B dhweb
is designed to run under systemd as the
.B dhweb.service
unit, not to be started manually. It is installed and enabled
automatically by
.BR install.sh .
.PP
The Configuration page mirrors
.BR dhedit 's
field list: callsign, license, name, address, latitude/longitude (with
the Maidenhead grid derived automatically), the Mapbox API token, the
AX Node password, the Winlink password, the default mode, and the
radio interface / rig control fields. The APRS password is derived
from the callsign and shown read\-only. Validation reuses the same
installed workers
.BR dhedit
does
.RI ( validcall.py ,
.IR validcoords.py ,
.IR maidenhead.py ,
.IR aprspass.py )
so the two editors never disagree about what a valid value looks like.
Saving backs up the previous
.I .dhinfo
contents to
.I .dhinfo.last
first, exactly like
.BR dhedit (1)
and
.BR install.sh .
.PP
The Mode page shows the current mode, the status of the systemd
service(s) it maps to, and a recent log tail, and can switch modes.
The Rig Control page shows the configured rig model/device/baud and
the status of
.BR dhrigctld (1),
and can turn CAT control on or off. Both pages run their respective
command
.RB ( dhmode (1)
or
.BR dhrig (1))
via a narrowly scoped NOPASSWD sudoers rule
.RI ( /etc/sudoers.d/digihub\-dhmode ,
written by
.BR install.sh )
that permits only those two scripts; both still validate their
arguments against a fixed whitelist before anything privileged
happens. Reading service status and logs requires
.B dhweb.service
to run with the
.B systemd\-journal
supplementary group, which
.B install.sh
also sets up.
.PP
The FLDigi page talks directly to FLDigi's own XML\-RPC control
interface
.RI ( 127.0.0.1:7362 ,
FLDigi's default) \-\- no sudoers rule is involved.
.B dhweb
never starts, stops, or otherwise manages the FLDigi process: FLDigi
is a GUI application with no headless mode, so it must already be
running locally (a monitor and keyboard, or your own remote desktop
session) with its XML\-RPC server enabled (on by default). If FLDigi
isn't reachable, the page says so and shows the command to start it.
When it is, the page shows version/TX\-RX\-status/modem/frequency and
can change the modem, set the frequency, and trigger TX/RX/abort.
.PP
Configuration is supplied entirely through environment variables,
normally set via the unit's EnvironmentFile
.RI ( /etc/digihub/web.env ):
.TP
.B DigiHubvenv
Path to the DigiHub Python virtual environment
.TP
.B DigiHubWebHost
Address to bind to (default 0.0.0.0, i.e. all interfaces)
.TP
.B DigiHubWebPort
TCP port to listen on (default 8080)
.PP
.B dhweb
performs no authentication and is intended to be reachable only from a
trusted local network (e.g. the same Wi\-Fi or hotspot the DigiHub
device itself is on). Do not expose it to the open internet.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check the running service's status and recent log output:
.B systemctl status dhweb
.br
.B journalctl \-u dhweb \-f
.TP
Open the Configuration page from a browser on the same network:
.B http://<digihub\-host>:8080/config
.TP
Open the Mode page:
.B http://<digihub\-host>:8080/mode
.TP
Open the Rig Control page:
.B http://<digihub\-host>:8080/rig
.TP
Open the FLDigi page:
.B http://<digihub\-host>:8080/fldigi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/digihub/web.env
Environment file supplying the variables above; written by
.BR install.sh .
.TP
.I /etc/sudoers.d/digihub\-dhmode
NOPASSWD rule permitting
.I /usr/local/bin/dhmode
and
.I /usr/local/bin/dhrig
only, used by the Mode and Rig Control pages; written by
.BR install.sh .
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/dhweb.service
The systemd unit that runs this service.
.TP
.I /usr/local/lib/digihub/dhweb
Installed Flask application (app.py, dhinfo.py, fldigi_client.py,
templates, static assets), kept in sync by
.BR dhupdate (1).
.TP
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
.TQ
.I $HOME/.dhinfo.last
Read and, on save, rewritten (with a backup) by the Configuration page.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.B dhweb
does not exit under normal operation; it serves requests until stopped
(e.g. by systemd).
.TP
.B 1
The shared UI library could not be loaded, the DigiHub Python virtual
environment (DigiHubvenv) was not found, or the installed application
.RI ( /usr/local/lib/digihub/dhweb/app.py )
is missing.
